{
  "doc_id": "60944",
  "text": "where N n is the number of particles with diameter between 1 and 10 nm, and k c (II) is the second order rate constant for coagulation of monodisperse aerosols. Note that k c (II) denotes the second order rate constant for coagulation, while k c stands for the pseudo-first order rate constant. To calculate the maximum loss rate, N n is evaluated for the time that the calculated nucleation rate is highest, and k c (II) is set to 2 Â 10 À9 cm 3 s À1 as an upper limit [CITATION_1] ].",
